n-named mobs in high level areas. Several steps in the combining and reported non-trivial at 252 skill<br><br>( Cue thread of 'Don't post unless you're gonna give us a full scale step-by-step guide and hold our hands! Let us waste time combining stuff that doesn't work, over and over and over! Damn you to hell for trying to help!' type posts :P ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>St BB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/24/02 3:19:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4782.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No need for a serubane spoiler.</span><hr size=1> If you are doing the seru bane quest, then you get the recipe while doing it. Not a hint not a puzzle, you are given exact instructions. That's all the spoiler anyone should need. <br><br>Spoilers are only needed when there is something ambiguous that people can't figure out in the context of the game easily.<br><br>Like where the hell Valdenov Zevfeer is (My guess is with elvis and Mayong Mistmoore sipping coco in Vexsar)<br><br>And also realize that seru bane requires you to have max smithing skill.<br><br>Ask any master smith how fun doing that is. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujondinsottovoce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jondin Sottovoce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/24/02 3:37:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScree